We made the ultimate VEGAN FRIED CHICKEN SANDWICH stacked with Creamy Coleslaw, Zesty Sauce, Fried Oyster Mushrooms, Pickles, Melted Cheese, all on a Toasted Gluten-Free bun! My hubby (who was OBSESSED with Chicken) says this Sandwich tastes better than any Fried Chicken that has ever graced his lips. 😋  VEGAN FRIED CHICKEN RECIPE: FLOUR BATTER: -Gluten-free Flour (2 Cups) -Nutritional Yeast (5 Tbs) -Poultry Seasoning (3 Tbs) -Onion Powder (2 Tbs) -Garlic Powder (2 Tbs) -Smoked Paprika (2 Tbs) -Pink Himalayan Salt (1-2 Tbs) -Crushed Black Pepper (1 Tbs)  EGG BATTER: -Vegan Egg (2.5 Cups Prepared) -Indian Black Salt (1 Tsp)  First: Soak the Oyster Mushrooms in Pickle Juice for 30 Minutes and then wrap it in wet Rice Paper to get the skin crispy. INSTRUCTIONS: 1. Place mushrooms in closed container with pickle juice to marinate in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes. 2. Heat oil on medium high to about 375 in a deep pan. 3. Mix together water and Vegan Egg in a large bowl until it has a very drippy liquid consistency. 4. Mix together in a separate large bowl the flour and all of your seasoning. 5. Drain pickle juice from mushrooms and dip mushrooms into egg mixture until coated.Tap off excess Vegan Egg. 6. 1 piece at a time cover Vegan Egg-covered mushrooms in your flour and seasoning mixture. 7. Deep fry Mushroom pieces in oil for until crispy and browned (about 3 to 5 minutes each piece). Drain on paper towels. 8. Feast, Sing, and Enjoy!  GREAT SAUCE: Mix Together: -1/3 Cup Vegan Mayo (I use @followyourheart brand) -3 Tbs Yellow Mustard -3 Tbs BBQ Sauce - - 🎥 GET THE FULL RECIPE AT http://www.youtube.com/user_36 👩🏽‍🍳Looking for more flavortastic recipes and soulful sounds? When I was a little kiddo, one of the first things I ever learned how to cook were ROASTED POTATO WEDGES. 🍠🥔🍠🥔 With this simple recipe you can roast the potatoes with ANY seasoning that you like but for me I love using poultry seasoning and fresh herbs!⠀ ⠀ ROASTED POTATO WEDGES RECIPE:⠀ 1. Chop your Potato into ½ inch thick wedges.⠀ 2. In a medium bowl coat the potatoes with 3 Tbs of Grapeseed Oil or Aquafaba (Chickpea Liquid).⠀ 3. Season your Potato Wedges with 2 Tbs Garlic Powder and 2 Tbs Onion Powder. 1 Tbs Smoked Paprika and 2 Tbs Poultry Seasoning. Salt and Pepper to Taste.⠀ 4. Toss your Seasoned Potato Wedges until covered and place them flat on a parchment paper covered baking sheet.⠀ 5. Bake the Seasoned Potato Wedges at 450 degrees for 20-28 minutes.⠀ 6. Garnish with Fresh Herb of choice.⠀ 7. Feast, Sing, and Enjoy!⠀ ⠀ 👩🏽‍🍳Looking for more flavortastic recipes and soulful sounds?⠀ ⠀ GET MORE COLORFUL RECIPES AND SONGS HERE: http://www.youtube.com/user_36 ⠀ ⠀ SING ALONG WITH ME ON TIKTOK HERE: https://vm.tiktok.com/coXedL/⠀ ⠀ MUSICAL LIVE-STREAMING COOKING CLASS WITH ONE GREAT VEGAN⠀ EVERY SATURDAY AT 1PM CST⠀ TIKTOK LIVE + FACEBOOK LIVE + INSTAGRAM LIVE⠀ ⠀ #user_36 #potato #easyveganrecipes veganrecipes #veganfoodshare #potatoes⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ #vegan #glutenfree #plantbased #cookvegan #vegancookingclass #cookingshow #vegancookingshow #vegancooking #veganrecipeshare #plantprotein #veganrecipe #soulfood #singingchef #vegansinger #recipe #healthy #plantbasedchef #veganrecipevideos #musicalcooking #musical #veganchef #healthyrecipes #plantbasedmeals ⠀

CHEESE AND VEGGIE ENCHILADAS! 🔥🔥🔥 I’ve been wanting to make something with my leftover bell peppers and mushrooms so I made these sensational Cheese + Veggie Enchiladas with my homemade Enchilada Sauce. Gluten-Free, Soy-Free, Nut-Free, Vegan and Flavor-FULL! CHEESE AND VEGGIE ENCHILADAS RECIPE: 1. In a large pan: Heat up some oil with Chili Powder and Gluten-Free Flour.  2. Add in Tomato Sauce, Veggie Broth, Cumin Powder, Garlic Powder, Onion Powder, Salt.  3. Whisk everything together until incorporated and add in more Veggie Broth as you whisk to get the desired thickness of Enchilada Sauce.  4. On medium heat, continue to cook your Enchilada Sauce for 3-6 minutes, whisking occasionally to prevent it from burning.  5. In a large pan: Sauté down in some Grapeseed Oil, Diced Red Onion, Diced Red Bell Pepper, and Diced Mushrooms.  6. Add in Smoked Paprika, Tajin or any Chili Seasoning, Salt and Pepper to taste and mix everything together. Sauté until veggies are soft.  7. In the Rice or Corn Tortillas, add your Sautéed Veggies and Vegan Cheese. Roll up the tortillas and place them (loose fold DOWN) in a deep baking pan. ⠀ 8. Cover your Veggie and Cheese filled Tortillas with your Enchilada Sauce and top with Vegan Cheese of Choice.⠀ ⠀ 9. Bake the Enchiladas at 455 for 12-18 minutes.⠀ ⠀ 10. Top Enchiladas with Lime Juice and Chopped Cilantro.⠀ ⠀ 11. Feast, Sing, and Enjoy!⠀ ⠀ 👩🏽‍🍳Looking for more flavortastic recipes and soulful sounds?⠀ ⠀ GET MORE COLORFUL RECIPES AND SONGS HERE: http://www.youtube.com/user_36 ⠀ ⠀ SING ALONG WITH ME ON TIKTOK HERE: https://vm.tiktok.com/coXedL/⠀ ⠀ MUSICAL LIVE-STREAMING COOKING CLASS WITH ONE GREAT VEGAN⠀ EVERY SATURDAY AT 1PM CST⠀ TIKTOK LIVE + FACEBOOK LIVE + INSTAGRAM LIVE⠀ ⠀ 🔥RECIPE LINKS IN MY BIO⠀ ⠀ #user_36 #enchiladas #veganrecipes #veganfoodshare #dairyfree #soyfree #easyrecipe #glutenfreerecipes⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ #vegan #glutenfree #plantbased #cookvegan #vegancookingclass #cookingshow #vegancookingshow #vegancooking #veganrecipeshare #plantprotein #veganrecipe #soulfood #singingchef #vegansinger #recipe #healthy #plantbasedchef #veganmexicanfood #musicalcooking #musical #veganchef #blackchef⠀

BOUNTIFUL BUDDHA BOWL! 🌿🌿🌿 I love a big bowl of flavortastic veggies and since I had some Fingerling Potatoes and Chickpeas around, I figured I’d turn it into a Bountiful Buddha Bowl for a big lunch today. @user_36⠀ ⠀ BOUNTIFUL BUDDHA BOWL RECIPE:⠀ 1. Coat some Chopped Potatoes in Grapeseed Oil and Herb-filled Seasoning + Pink Himalayan Salt. ⠀ 2. Roast the potatoes for 15-20 minutes at 455 degrees.⠀ 3. Sauté some Cooked Chickpeas in: Poultry Seasoning, Smoked Paprika, Mustard Powder, Parsley Flakes, Salt, Pepper, and Coconut Milk.⠀ 4. Make your No-Honey Mustard by whisking together: Vegan Mayonnaise, Yellow Mustard, Maple Syrup, Apple Cider Vinegar, a splash of Cayenne Pepper, Salt + Pepper.⠀ 5. Load your Bountiful Buddha Bowl with: Arugula, Roasted Potatoes, Sautéed Chickpeas, Buttery Rice, Avocado Slices, No-Honey Mustard, and Green Onion.⠀ 6. THAI SPICE RAINBOW RICE 🌈 This was my first time ever cooking with Tempeh and I used a sweet and spicy Thai Spice Marinade to make this feast colorful, hearty, and so delish! Also, I love to use the Thai Spice Sauce with Mushrooms or Jackfruit if you're looking for another meaty option. 🎥 (Full Recipe video on my TikTok page!)⠀ ⠀ THAI SPICE RAINBOW RICE :⠀ THAI SPICE SAUCE:⠀ Organic Sriracha (3 Tbs-1/4 cup) ⠀ Liquid Aminos (1/4 Cup)⠀ Rice Vinegar (1/3 Cup)⠀ Lime Juice (3 Tbs)⠀ Garlic Powder (1 Tbs)⠀ Onion Powder (1 Tbs)⠀ Ground Ginger (2 Tsp)⠀ Maple Syrup (1.5 Tbs)⠀ Black Pepper (2 Tsp)⠀ Pink Hemilayan Salt (ONLY IF NEEDED!)⠀ Minced Garlic (1.5 Tbs)⠀ ⠀ ADDITIONAL INGREDIENTS:⠀ Tempeh or Mushrooms ⠀ Any Rice of Choice⠀ Romaine Lettuce⠀ Sliced Cucumbers⠀ Sliced Carrots⠀ Chopped Cabbage⠀ Crushed Peanuts (1/4 Cup)⠀ Chopped Green Onion (1/4 Cup)⠀ Lime Slices⠀ ⠀ INSTRUCTIONS:⠀ 1. In a bowl combine all of your THAI SPICE SAUCE ingredients and whisk until combined.⠀ 2. Using a splash of Veggie Broth, cook your Tempeh or Mushrooms In a large pan until the are mostly cooked.⠀ 3. Pour your THAI SPICE SAUCE into your pan and cover. Let it cook on medium high for about 3-6 minutes. ⠀ 4.Load up your plate with Vegetables, Rice, and Cooked Tempeh or Mushrooms⠀ 5. Sprinkle Crushed Peanuts and Fresh Mint on top. ⠀ 6. Sing, serve, and enjoy!⠀ ⠀ 👩🏽‍🍳Looking for more flavortastic recipes and soulful sounds?⠀ ⠀ GET MORE COLORFUL RECIPES AND SONGS HERE: http://www.youtube.com/user_36 ⠀ ⠀ SING ALONG WITH ME ON TIKTOK HERE: https://vm.tiktok.com/coXedL/⠀ ⠀ MUSICAL LIVE-STREAMING COOKING CLASS WITH ONE GREAT VEGAN⠀ EVERY SATURDAY AT 1PM CST⠀ TIKTOK LIVE + FACEBOOK LIVE + INSTAGRAM LIVE⠀ ⠀ 🔥ALL RECIPE LINKS IN MY BIO⠀ ⠀ 📷 Photo by my king @aceshotthat ⠀ ⠀ #user_36 #thaifood #veganrecipes #veganfoodshare #tempeh #veganprotein⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ #vegan #glutenfree #plantbased #cookvegan #vegancookingclass #cookingshow #vegancookingshow #vegancooking #veganrecipeshare #plantprotein #veganrecipe #soulfood #singingchef #vegansinger #recipe #healthy #plantbasedchef #veganthaifood #musicalcooking #musical #veganchef

MUSHROOM STEAK TACOS! 🌮🌮🌮 I had fun cooking up this protein-packed recipe for a hearty, flavortastic, and easy lunch. Tacos are one of my favorite quick gluten-free and #veganlunch meals because you can fill up a corn tortilla with so many different veggies, beans, spices, and sauces. The possibilities are truly endless! @user_36⠀ ⠀ MUSHROOM STEAK TACOS RECIPE:⠀ 1. In a pan Sauté down Chopped White Onions in Vegan Butter and Pink Himalayan Slat until soft and clear.⠀ 2. Add in large Oyster Mushrooms and coat them in Butter + Onions⠀ 3. Add in Smoked Paprika, Liquid Smoke, Ground Mustard, Black Pepper, Ground Cumin, Cajun Seasoning, and more Pink Himalayan Salt if needed.⠀ 4. Pour in a splash of Veggie Broth and press your mushrooms flat in the pan with another pan. (I suggest weighing it down with some cans on top of your pan!)⠀ 5. Add in Chickpeas/Garbanzo Beans and incorporated the beans with the spices + mushroom liquid in your pan. Cover and let it cook on medium high for 5 minutes.⠀ 6. Build your taco with Purple Cabbage, Chickpeas, Mushroom Steak, Lime Crema (Vegan Mayo, Lime Juice, Garlic Powder + Onion Powder, Salt) and a Fresh Herb of Choice.⠀ 7. CREAMY MUSHROOM + SUN-DRIED TOMATO PASTA. 🍅🍅🍅 Y’all, I’ve got a craving for carbzzzzz. Anyone else? That’s why I whipped up this hearty and extra creamy Mushroom + Sun-Dried Tomato Pasta. @user_36⠀ ⠀ CREAMY MUSHROOM + SUN-DRIED TOMATO PASTA RECIPE:⠀ -Cook your noodles of choice (I used Gluten Free @sprouts brand) in water and a bit of oil. ⠀ -In a large pan: Sauté down some Diced White Onions (1/2 Onion) in Vegan Butter (3-4 Tbs) (I used @meltorganic brand) until clear. Halfway through, add in Minced Garlic (2 Tbs).⠀ -Once Everything is clear and cooked down, add in Chopped Mushrooms (1.5 Cups Chopped) into your pan and sauté them until soft.⠀ -Add in Sun-Dried Tomatoes (1 Cup) and Italian Seasoning (3-4 Tbs) of Choice to the pan.⠀ -Add in Full Fat Coconut Milk (1 Cup) and a little bit of Tomato Sauce (1/4 Cup) to your pan. ⠀ -Add in Maple Syrup (1-2 Tbs) , Nutritional Yeast (3 Tbs) + Salt and Pepper to taste in your pan.⠀ -Mix all of your ingredients together and cover your pan. Cook on medium-high for 5-8 Minutes⠀ -Build your pasta with Noodles, Creamy Mushroom Sauce, @followyourheart Mozzarella, Fresh Herb if choice⠀ -Feast, Sing, and Enjoy!⠀ ⠀ 👩🏽‍🍳Looking for more flavortastic recipes and soulful sounds?⠀ ⠀ GET MORE COLORFUL RECIPES AND SONGS HERE: http://www.youtube.com/user_36 ⠀ ⠀ SING ALONG WITH ME ON TIKTOK HERE: https://vm.tiktok.com/coXedL/⠀ ⠀ MUSICAL LIVE-STREAMING COOKING CLASS WITH ONE GREAT VEGAN⠀ EVERY SATURDAY AT 1PM CST⠀ TIKTOK LIVE + FACEBOOK LIVE + INSTAGRAM LIVE⠀ ⠀ 🔥ALL RECIPE LINKS IN MY BIO⠀ ⠀ 📷 Photos by my king @aceshotthat ⠀ ⠀ #user_36 #pasta #veganrecipes #veganfoodshare⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ #vegan #glutenfree #plantbased #cookvegan #vegancookingclass #cookingshow #vegancookingshow #vegancooking #veganrecipeshare #plantprotein #veganrecipe #soulfood #singingchef #vegansinger #recipe #healthy #plantbasedchef #healthyfood #musicalcooking #musical #veganchef⠀

BBQ BEAN CHILI 🔥🔥🔥 Check out this quick and easy #protein packed recipe for Barbecue Bean Chili. Took me less than 15 minutes to make!⠀ ⠀ BBQ BEAN CHILI RECIPE:⠀ -Diced Red Onion (1/2 Onion)⠀ -Vegetarian Baked Beans + Liquid (I used @bushsbeans brand) (1 Cup)⠀ -Cooked Chickpeas (1 Cup)⠀ -Cooked Pinto Beans (1 Cup)⠀ -Diced Tomatoes + Juice (1 Cup)⠀ -Chili Seasoning (2 Tbs)⠀ -Smoked Paprika (1 Tbs)⠀ -Nutritional Yeast (1.5 Tbs)⠀ -Cumin (2 Tsp)⠀ -Salt and Pepper to Taste⠀ -Chopped Fresh Parsley or Cilantro (1/4 Cup)⠀ ⠀ In a large pot or instant-pot:⠀ -Cook onion down until clear.⠀ -Add in all of your ingredients.⠀ -Mix up spices and beans until everything is incorporated.⠀ -Cover the pot with lid and cook on medium high for 5-8 minutes. ⠀ -Feast, Sing, and Enjoy!⠀ ⠀ PS. THAI SPICE STIR FRY! Have you tried this easy and delicious recipe yet? With this #recipe it’s ALLLLL about that Thai Spice Sauce. What’s also fierce is that you can use this Sauce on any Vegetables, Noodles, Rice, or Plant-Protein you want and this meal will always turn out flavorful and delicious! (YOUTUBE VIDEO LINK IN MY BIO!) @user_36⠀ ⠀ WATCH THE COOKING CLASS VIDEO HERE: https://youtu.be/iRPkvcnVdzc⠀ ⠀ DOWNLOAD THE FULL RECIPE HERE: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1DLTZ8G6zFU4_naD-S5OcB1dOFcpUyK-c/view?usp=drivesdk⠀ ⠀ 🔥THAI SPICE STIR FRY RECIPE:⠀ THAI SPICE SAUCE:⠀ Organic Sriracha (3 Tbs-1/4 cup) ⠀ Liquid Aminos (1/4 Cup)⠀ Rice Vinegar (1/3 Cup)⠀ Lime Juice (3 Tbs)⠀ Ground Ginger (2 Tsp)⠀ Maple Syrup (1.5 Tbs)⠀ Black Pepper (2 Tsp)⠀ Pink Hemilayan Salt (ONLY IF NEEDED!)⠀ Minced Garlic (1.5 Tbs)⠀ Vegetable Broth OR Coconut Milk (1/4 Cup or more for Soup)⠀ (OPTIONAL) Peanut Butter (1.5 Tbs)⠀ ⠀ ADDITIONAL INGREDIENTS:⠀ Any Noodles or Rice of Choice (2 Cups Cooked)⠀ Any Vegetables and Plant Protein of Choice (2 Cups)⠀ Crushed Peanuts (1/4 Cup)⠀ Chopped Green Onion (1/4 Cup)⠀ I used @allvegetarianinc shrimp! ⠀ ⠀ INSTRUCTIONS:⠀ 1. In a bowl combine all of your THAI SPICE SAUCE ingredients and whisk until combined.⠀ 2. Using a splash of Veggie Broth, cook your chosen Vegetables and Plant-Protein in a large pan until the are mostly cooked.⠀ 3. Pour your THAI SPICE SAUCE into your pan with your Vegetables and cover. Let it cook on medium high for about 3-6 minutes. ⠀ 4.Cook your Noodles or Rice and add them into your pan. ⠀ 5. Sprinkle Crushed Peanuts and Green Onion on top. ⠀ 6. SHRIMP + BLACK BEAN TOSTADAS 🍤🍤🍤 From the mind of @aceshotthat and his cravings! This recipe is crazy easy to make and only took about 15 minutes to create from beginning to end. Also, you can swap out the Black Beans for Pinto Beans or use both! ⠀ ⠀ SHRIMP + BLACK BEAN TOSTADA RECIPE:⠀ -Red Onion (1/2 Onion) -Minced Garlic (1.5 Tbs) -Grapeseed Oil or Veggie Broth (2-3 Tbs) -Pink Himalayan Salt (1/2-1 Tbs) -Black Pepper (1/4 Tbs) -Black Beans (2 Cups -Smoked Paprika (2 Tbs) -Garlic Powder (1/2 Tbs) -Onion Powder (1/2 Tbs) -Ground Cumin (2 Tsp) -Chili Powder (2-3 Tsp) -Maple Syrup (1 Tbs) -Vegan Shrimp from @allvegetarianinc (10 Shrimp) -Lime Juice (1.5 Tbs) -Chopped Lettuce⠀ -Freshly Diced Tomato⠀ -Pickled Jalapeños⠀ -Corn Tostadas (5-8 Tostadas) ⠀ LIME CREMA⠀ Mix Together:⠀ -1/3 Cup Vegan Mayo⠀ -2 Tbs Lime Juice⠀ -1 Tbs Garlic Powder⠀ -1 Tbs Onion Powder⠀ -1/2 Tbs Plant-Based Milk⠀ -Salt + Pepper to Taste⠀  1. In a large pot cook down your Red Onions in Oil or Veggie Broth until the are sautéd and clear. Add in Minced Garlic halfway through cooking down your Red Onions. 2. Add to your pot the Black Beans and all seasoning. Stir your ingredients together until well incorporated. 3. Cover your pot with a lid and let the Beans cook on medium-high for 6-10 minutes. 4. In a pan sauté your Vegan Shrimp with a splash of Lime Juice and Season with Chili Powder and Salt + Pepper to taste. 5. Build your Tostada with Chopped Lettuce, Zesty Beans, Diced Tomatoes, Shrimp, Jalapeños, and Lime Crema. 👩🏽‍🍳Looking for more flavortastic recipes and soulful sounds?⠀ ⠀ GET MORE COLORFUL RECIPES AND SONGS HERE: http://www.youtube.com/user_36 ⠀ ⠀ SING ALONG WITH ME ON TIKTOK HERE: https://vm.tiktok.com/coXedL/⠀ ⠀ MUSICAL LIVE-STREAMING COOKING CLASS WITH ONE GREAT VEGAN⠀ EVERY SATURDAY AT 1PM CST⠀ TIKTOK LIVE + FACEBOOK LIVE + INSTAGRAM LIVE⠀ ⠀ 🔥ALL RECIPE LINKS IN MY BIO⠀ ⠀ 📷 Photo by my king @aceshotthat ⠀ ⠀ #user_36 #veganrecipes #veganfoodshare⠀ #vegan #glutenfree #plantbased #cookvegan #vegancookingclass #cookingshow #vegancookingshow #vegancooking #veganrecipeshare #plantprotein #veganrecipe #soulfood #singingchef #vegansinger #recipe #healthy #plantbased

I love eating the color #purple in whatever way I can and I was so pumped when these Purple Potato Fries came out perfectly!⠀ ⠀ PURPLE POTATO FRIES RECIPE:⠀ -Chopped Purple Potato (Whole Potato)⠀ -Grapeseed Oil (3-4 Tbs for coating potatoes) ⠀ -Cornstarch (3 Tbs)⠀ -Seasoning of Choice (2 Tbs)⠀ -Pink Himalayan Salt (2 Tsp)⠀ -Grapeseed Oil (2 Cups for frying)⠀ -Pink Himalayan Salt (1-2 Tsp to finish)⠀ ⠀ 1. VEGAN RANCH! 🌿 Classic Ranch seems to make ANY meal irresistible nah? I’ve been perfecting this Creamy Vegan Ranch Recipe because we love to jazz up a lot of big salads (and French Fries) with delish dips + dressings for our big #intermittentfasting meal of the day! ⠀ ⠀ CREAMY VEGAN RANCH RECIPE:⠀ -1 Cup of Vegan Mayonnaise (I use soy-free @followyourheart brand)⠀ -2 Tsp Lemon Juice⠀ -1/2 Tbs Onion Powder⠀ -1/2 Tbs Garlic Powder⠀ -1 Tsp Dried Dill⠀ -1 Tsp Dried Parsley⠀ -2 Tsp Nutritional Yeast⠀ -1-3 Tsp of Salt + Pepper⠀ -2 Tbs Plant Milk (use more if you want the ranch more liquidity!)⠀ ⠀ I like to add all of my ingredients into a small jar and shake it up until all of the spices are mixed in. Make a big jar of this creamy comfort and save your Ranch in the fridge for up to 4 weeks!⠀ ⠀ This simple #vegan ranch is perfect for Pizzas, Salads, Nachos, Buddha Bowls, and more! Cook down the Onions in Veggie Broth until clear and soft.⠀ 2. Add in all over Veggies and sauté + add in your Seasonings⠀ 3. Add more Veggie Broth and cover + simmer for 5-8 minutes.⠀ 4. CHICKPEA + JACKFRUIT CURRY 🔥Such a soulful recipe made from just a few #pantry stable ingredients! This Curry is just what you need for your spirit and soul!⠀ (YOUTUBE VIDEO LINK IN MY BIO!)👈🏼⠀ ⠀ CHICKPEA + JACKFRUIT CURRY RECIPE:⠀ -Grapeseed Oil OR Aquafaba (2 Tbs)⠀ -Cooked Chickpeas (1 Cup)⠀ -Chopped Jackfruit (1 Cup)⠀ -Quinoa (1 Cup)⠀ -Green Chilis (1/3 Cup)⠀ -Curry Powder (2.5 Tbs)⠀ -Ground Nutmeg (1-2 Tsp)⠀ -Ground Ginger (2-3 Tsp)⠀ -Smoked Paprika (1 Tbs)⠀ -Maple Syrup (1.5 Tbs)⠀ -Hot Sauce of Choice (1-4 Tsp)⠀ -Pink Himalayan Salt (1-2 Tbs)⠀ -Black Pepper (1/2-1 Tbs)⠀ -Parsley Flakes (1/2 Tbs)⠀ -Coconut Milk (1.5 Cups)⠀ ⠀ -Veggie Broth (2 Cups)⠀ -Diced White Onion (1/2 Cup)⠀ -Minced Garlic (1 Tbs)⠀ ⠀ TAHINI CREAM⠀ -Tahini (1/4 Cup)⠀ -Pink Himalayan Salt (½-1 Tbs)⠀ -Lemon Juice (3 Tbs)⠀ -Nutritional Yeast (2 Tbs)⠀ -Veggie Broth or Plant Milk ( 1/2-1 Cup)⠀ -Garlic Powder (1/2 Tbs)⠀ -Onion Powder (1/2 Tbs)⠀ ⠀ INSTRUCTIONS:⠀ 1. In a large pot cook down your White Onions in Grapeseed Oil or Aquafaba until they are soft and clear. ⠀ 2. In the same large pot start by adding the Coconut Milk and Quinoa and then add in all of the other ingredients. ⠀ 3. Make sure that your ingredients are pushed below the liquid line so that all of the Beans and Jackfruit can cook in the broth. Add more Veggie Broth/Coconut Milk if needed. ⠀ 4. Let the Curry cook covered on medium high for 15-25 minutes or until the quinoa is soft and fully cooked⠀ 5. Mix together your ingredients for the TAHINI CREAM until fully blended together. ⠀ 6. Top off your cooked Curry with the TAHINI CREAM and add fresh lime and green onions for garnish!⠀ ⠀ 👩🏽‍🍳 Looking for flavortastic recipes that help you get your glow on? 🎶 You can find music-infused recipes and live-lyrical classes on my YouTube Channel: One Great Vegan ⠀ ⠀ 🎥 http://Youtube.Com/user_36⠀ ⠀ Photos by my King @aceshotthat ⠀ ⠀ #user_36 #veganfood #veganchef #plantbased #veganrecipeshare #veganrecipes #whatveganseat #glutenfreevegan #vegancooking #cookingshow #vegancookingshow #curry #jackfruit #vegancookingclass #vegancurry #musicalvegan #plantbased #vegansinger #singingchef #musicalcookingshow #cookingclass

Craving something DELISH? 🧆 I just made some Creamy Alfredo + Meatballs with some Perfect Parmesan! #SoyFree, #GlutenFree, Flavor-Full, and #Protein Packed. (YOUTUBE RECIPE LINK IN BIO!)⠀ ⠀ WATCH THE RECIPE VIDEO HERE: https://youtu.be/ClTREv-Sdx0⠀ ⠀ DOWNLOAD THE RECIPE HERE: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ZO8X4tZ16Wc-heRWkgFIzI78XpFgFaOh/view⠀ ⠀ RECIPE:⠀ Gluten Free Pasta (2 Cups)⠀ Chopped Fresh Parsley (1/3 Cup)⠀ @beyondmeat Sausage (1 Package)⠀ ⠀ CASHEW ALFREDO SAUCE ⠀ Soaked Raw Cashews OR Boiled White Potatoes (1 Cup)⠀ Coconut Milk (2 Cups)⠀ Veggie Broth (1/2 Cup)⠀ Minced Garlic (2 Tbs)⠀ Maple Syrup (1.5 Tbs)⠀ Lemon Juice (3 Tbs)⠀ Nutritional Yeast (1/3 Cup)⠀ Pink Himalayan Salt (1-2Tbs)⠀ Black Pepper (1-2 Tsp)⠀ Garlic Powder (2 Tbs)⠀ Onion Powder (2 Tbs)⠀ ⠀ PERFECT PARMESAN:⠀ Raw Cashews (1/2 Cup)⠀ NutritionalYeast (1/3 Cup)⠀ Indian Black Salt (1-2Tsp)⠀ Black Pepper (1-2 Tsp)⠀ Garlic Powder (2 Tbs)⠀ Onion Powder (2 Tbs)⠀ Directions: Pulse together Perfect Parmesan Ingredients in a food processor until fully incorporated. ⠀ ⠀ INSTRUCTIONS:⠀ 1. In a blender combine all of your ingredients for the CASHEW ALFREDO SAUCE until it is a smooth ranch-like consistancy. ⠀ 2. Warm CASHEW ALFREDO SAUCE covered in a medium pot on medium-low heart. ⠀ 3. Cook your Gluten-Free Noodles⠀ 4. Remove the skin from a Beyond Meat Sausage and in a large bowl mix together the Sausage Meat and the Chopped Fresh Parsley until incorporated.⠀ 5. Size out balls of meat with a spoon and roll the Meatballs in your hands until round.⠀ 6. In a large pan saute the Meatballs on all sides.⠀ 7. Build your pasta with Noodles, Cashew Sauce, Meatballs, and Fresh Parsley.⠀ ⠀ 👩🏽‍🍳 Looking for flavortastic recipes that help you get your glow on? 🎶 You can find music-infused recipes and live-lyrical classes on my YouTube Channel: One Great Vegan ⠀ ⠀ 🎥 http://Youtube.Com/user_36⠀ ⠀ 👉🏼 YOUTUBE LINK IN THE BIO⠀ ⠀ 📷 Photos by my king @aceshotthat⠀ ⠀ #user_36 #veganrecipes #cookingclass #vegan #livestreaming #vegancookingclass #livestream #vegancooking #veganrecipeshare #musicalcookingshow

This JAMBALAYA is FIRE! 🔥 Coconut + Sausage #jambalaya is classic soul-food in a bowl and what is fierce is that you can make this zesty recipe in just one pot!⠀ ⠀ Coconut + Sausage Jambalaya Recipe⠀ -1/2 White Onion⠀ -3 Tbs Grapeseed Oil or Veggie Broth⠀ -2.5 Cups Coconut Milk⠀ -1 Can of Kidney Beans (with juice!)⠀ -1 Bag of Frozen Peas⠀ -2 Cups of Rice⠀ -2 Tbs Maple Syrup⠀ -3 Tbs Cajun Seasoning⠀ -1 Tbs Smoked Paprika⠀ -2 Tbs Nutritional Yeast⠀ -1/2 Tbs-2 Tbs Hot Sauce of Choice⠀ -Chopped Sausage from @beyondmeat⠀ -Salt and Pepper to your personal taste⠀ ⠀ 1. Cook Onions and Oil until onions are soft and clear. ⠀ 2. Add in Coconut Milk and Rice then mix. ⠀ 3. Add in all other Ingredients and mix.⠀ 4. Cover pot and let Jambalaya cook until rice is done.⠀ 5. Feast and enjoy!⠀ ⠀ Time to get in the kitchen and get glowing. Let me know how your Jambalaya turns out and stay safe at home everyone! 💕⠀ ⠀ 👩🏽‍🍳 Looking for flavortastic recipes that help you get your glow on? ✨How do you get your #GLOW on? To glow means to find overall health and peace within yourself and share that glow by being an example of love. ⠀ ⠀ ✨Well, actually it goes a bit deeper than that. When I was 17 years old I was confronted with the reality that life is short and that mental illness runs rampant in my family. At that moment I had to make a choice:⠀ 1. Wallow in the tragedy and let that darkness consume the rest of my life.⠀ 2. Find light through the pain by accepting my illnesses, insecurities, and past abuse.⠀ ⠀ ✨I chose to accept my truth. No matter how ugly, wicked, and sick my birth mother’s mind was, and despite how crippling the fear that I too could have bipolar schizophrenia, I made the choice to accept that mental illness was a part of me and I would not let that illness define my life as Gabrielle Reyes.⠀ ⠀ ✨By finding peace with my past, discovering the healing power of eating plants, and discovering the joy of an honest sexual relationship I feel that glow more and more everyday and strive to dig deeper within my self everyday!⠀ ⠀ ✨So, how DO you get your glow on?⠀ 1. Strive for mental health and wellness through truth.⠀ 2. Heal your body with plants and a variety of colors.⠀ 3. Aim for sexual health and honesty in all relationships. ⠀ ✨Try out these three tips and let me know how you feel when you open your life to truth, possibilities, and overall health! ⠀ ⠀ 📷 Photo by @aceshotthat ⠀ ⠀ #user_36 #getyourglowon #mentalhealthawareness⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ #mentalhealth #vegan #plantsheal #healthandwellness #veganchef #plantbased #plantpowered #romance #ruth #relationships #vegans #veganactress #vegancookingshow #veganglow #veganlife #healing #wordsofwisdom #veganbody #vegangoals #vegancooking #cookingshow #vegancookingclass

Going #ZEROWASTE one day at a time! 🌏 Today I’m trying out a new way to clean my mason jars that I adore using for #sustainable storage and of course for, my big glasses of daily fresh celery juice! 💚⠀ ⠀ 💥 So, I was doing a bit of deep cleaning and I just discovered a fabulous way to remove that pesky glue that gets stuck to glass jars under the sticker. ⠀ ⠀ 🍊 ORANGE GOO-GONE RECIPE ⠀ -1 Part Melted Coconut Oil⠀ -2 Parts Baking Soda⠀ -1 Tsp Orange Essential Oil⠀ ⠀ ✨ Now mix that baby up! Make sure the mixture is thick like a paste and stick the Orange Goo-Gone onto the spot where the glue is stuck. Let the mixture sit on the jar overnight. Wash off the mixture with a sponge, warm soap, and water and get a sparkling clean, ready to fill with goodies! ⠀ ⠀ 🌿 Every year we made it our goal to use less and less waste and choose glass/wood/metal over plastic containers. It’s been challenging but overall a fun learning experience!⠀ ⠀ 👩🏽‍🍳 Looking for helpful tips and epic food that helps you get your glow on? 💚Celery Juice keeps you feeling SEXY! Have you tried fresh celery juice yet? ⠀ ⠀ ✨My loves, you all KNOW my obsession with #celeryjuice is real and every day that I drink this green magic I feel alive and renewed! Inspired by @medicalmedium and inspiring my friends and family to start drinking this green goodness has seriously become a passion of mine because I feel the positive affects of fresh celery juice on the daily!⠀ ⠀ 🍃 Benefits of Celery Juice:⠀ -Activates the gut for better digestion⠀ -Natural anti-inflammatory⠀ -Aids the Liver⠀ -Fights infections⠀ -Promotes Cardiovascular Health⠀ -Skin healing⠀ -Improves sleep and mental clarity⠀ -Clears up skin⠀ -Hydrating⠀ ⠀ ✌🏼 I suggest investing in a juicer (I bought one at @target for $70 and it’s lasted me 7 years!) and juice 1 full stalk of celery + 1 big pink lady apple 5 times a week. I also like to drink it first thing in the morning because I’ve found that it helps keep me full and energized until I dive into a huge plant-based lunch around 1PM.⠀ ⠀ 💚 If you are looking for a inexpensive way to keep the doctor away TRY CELERY JUICE. 🌮 Vegan tacos are the answer! 🌮 One of the easiest foods to veganize is the classic taco! There are so many different styles, fillings, and sauces that you can stuff into the perfect shell.⠀ ⠀ ✨To build the perfectly colorful taco just:⠀ ⠀ -Pick your Shell: Corn, Flour, Lettuce/Collards ⠀ ⠀ -Spread on a Sauce: Zesty Hummus, Cashew Cream, Sriracha, Guacamole⠀ ⠀ -Pick your Hearty Element: Roasted Potatoes, Marinated Mushrooms, Seasoned Jackfruit, Fried Oyster Mushrooms, Cauliflower Wings, Grilled Veggies, Vegan Meat Replacement⠀ ⠀ -Pick your Stuffing: Rice, Beans, Quinoa, Grilled Peppers, Corn⠀ ⠀ -Pick a Fresh Element: Avocado, Salsa, Pico, Pineapple, Mango, Pomegranate ⠀ ⠀ -Finish with a Fresh Herb: Cilantro, Green Onion, Parsley, Arugula, Micro Greens⠀ ⠀ -Add a lime or lemon slice for an extra splash of acidity.⠀ ⠀ 😋 With this combo of layers and ingredients you can make hundreds of different kinds of tasty taco creations. Cold Weather = Marinara Time! 🔥 On a cold day I love to cozy up to a big bowl of brown rice pasta made made with my hearty marinara sauce and the COVERED in @followyourheart vegan cheese. Want to know the secret to my sauce? Maple syrup! The sweetness of the syrup balances out the acidity from the tomatoes and makes this sauce positivity perfect!⠀ ⠀ RECIPE - Hearty Marinara Sauce:⠀ -2 Tbs Aquafaba or Grapeseed Oil⠀ -1 Diced White Onion ⠀ -Package of Beyond Beef from @beyondmeat ⠀ -3 Cups Tomato Sauce ⠀ -1.5 Tbs Minced Garlic⠀ -2 Tbs Fresh Chopped Parsley⠀ -1.5 Tbs Onion Powder⠀ -1.5 Tbs Garlic Powder⠀ -1/2 Tbs Smoked Paprika⠀ -2 Tbs Maple Syrup⠀ ⠀ DIRECTIONS:⠀ In a large and deep pan sauté the White Onion in Aquafaba and add in Beyond Beef. Sauté Beyond Beef and Onions until cooked down and the beef is slightly browned. Add in Minced Garlic, Tomato Sauce and ALL the other seasoning. Let the sexy sauce simmer covered on medium-low for about 8-10 minutes and serve!⠀ ⠀ I use this Hearty Marinara Sauce for Lasanga, Stuffed Mushrooms, Spaghetti Squash and so many more colorful home cooked recipes!⠀ ⠀ 👩🏽‍🍳 Looking for flavortastic recipes full of color? When you are cooking colorful you are cooking GREAT! 🌈⠀ ⠀ One of my best bits of advise for people who ask me how to go vegan is to EAT THE RAINBOW. 🌿 GREEN glorious green! My obsession with #celeryjuice has been going on for 9 months now and I feel like a changed woman. And my Song of Celery Juice is the JAM y’all! 🎵⠀ ⠀ 🌱 Honestly, when I first heard about drinking celery juice for your health I thought it was just another fad cleanse that sounded like A LOT of work that I wasn’t willing to commit to consistently. 🍎 But, the first time I added a big pink lady apple into my celery juice it changed the game. 😍 The sweetness of the apple gives the drink a light, refreshing, and tasty flavor that cuts the earthy flavor of the celery.⠀ ⠀ 🍃 Benefits of Celery Juice:⠀ -Activates the gut for better digestion⠀ -Natural anti-inflammatory⠀ -Aids the Liver⠀ -Fights infections⠀ -Promotes Cardiovascular Health⠀ -Skin healing⠀ -Improves sleep and mental clarity⠀ -Hydrating⠀ ⠀ ✌🏼 I suggest investing in a juicer (I bought one at @target for $70 and it’s lasted me 7 years!) and juice 1 full stalk of celery + 1 big pink lady apple 5 times a week. I also like to drink it first thing in the morning because I’ve found that it helps keep me full and energized until I dive into a huge plant-based lunch around 1PM.⠀ ⠀ 💚 If you are looking for a inexpensive way to keep the doctor away TRY CELERY JUICE. Oh! And don’t forget to get your groove on when you are juicing this magic green drank.⠀ ⠀ 🎶 Celery juice, celery juice, I’m drinkin’ me some celery juice! 🎵⠀ #user_36 #veganrecipes #celeryjuicebenefits⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ .⠀ #celeryjuiceheals #celeryjuicechallenge #getyourglowon #medicalmedium #freshjuice @celeryjuicebenefits @celeryjuiceheals @medicalmedium
